---
// src/pages/illusions/chromatic-aberration.astro
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Chromostereopsis — Optical Illusion Lab" 
  description="Explore the science, history, and visual parameters of the Chromostereopsis optical illusion."
>
  <div class="py-12 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 max-w-7xl mx-auto space-y-12">
    <!-- Breadcrumb back navigation -->
    <nav class="flex text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-wider text-slate-400 space-x-2 pb-2 border-b border-indigo-500/10">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">Home</a>
      <span>/</span>
      <span class="text-purple-400">Chromostereopsis</span>
    </nav>

    <!-- Hero Header -->
    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center justify-between gap-6 pb-6">
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <div class="flex items-center space-x-2">
          <span class="text-xs font-black px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full bg-indigo-500/10 text-indigo-400 border border-indigo-500/20 uppercase tracking-wider">Color</span>
          <span class="text-xs font-black px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full bg-purple-500/10 text-purple-400 border border-purple-500/20 uppercase tracking-wider">🟡 Medium</span>
        </div>
        <h1 class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-black tracking-tight text-slate-900 dark:text-white">
          Chromostereopsis
        </h1>
        <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-350 text-base max-w-2xl font-medium">
          Discover how the brain interprets this fascinating color visual puzzle.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- LARGE INTERACTIVE DEMO -->
    <div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center py-6 border-b border-indigo-500/10">
      <div class="w-full max-w-[600px] mx-auto space-y-4">
        <div class="relative flex flex-col items-center justify-center h-96 w-full bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-950/40 rounded-xl overflow-hidden border border-indigo-500/10 p-6">
          <svg class="w-56 h-40 select-none bg-black rounded-lg" viewBox="0 0 240 120">
            <g stroke-width="2.5" fill="none">
              <circle cx="120" cy="60" r="45" stroke="#3b82f6" />
              <circle cx="120" cy="60" r="30" stroke="#ef4444" />
              <path d="M 120,60 L 120,10" stroke="#ef4444" />
              <path d="M 120,60 L 120,110" stroke="#3b82f6" />
              <path d="M 120,60 L 70,60" stroke="#ef4444" />
              <path d="M 120,60 L 170,60" stroke="#3b82f6" />
            </g>
            <circle cx="120" cy="60" r="4" fill="#ffffff" />
          </svg>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Content Split Layout -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-12 pt-4">
      <!-- Left 2-Columns -->
      <div class="lg:col-span-2 space-y-10">
        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-black text-slate-900 dark:text-white flex items-center space-x-2">
            <span class="text-purple-500">🧠</span>
            <span>THE SCIENCE</span>
          </h2>
          <div class="prose prose-indigo dark:prose-invert text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed text-xs sm:text-sm font-semibold text-justify">
            <p>Chromostereopsis is a visual phenomenon where different colors on a dark background appear to lie in different depth planes. When red and blue lines are displayed side-by-side on a black screen, red shapes appear to float forward, while blue shapes recede into the distance. This depth illusion is caused by chromatic aberration in the eye's lens. Because different wavelengths of light refract at slightly different angles as they pass through the lens, red light (longer wavelength) and blue light (shorter wavelength) focus on slightly different points on the retina. The brain is forced to adjust focus dynamically between the two colors. The disparity is interpreted by our binocular depth-calculation systems in the visual cortex as a difference in physical distance. The strength of this depth illusion varies among individuals, but it remains a primary example of how optical physics and sensory neuroscience interact to construct our three-dimensional visual reality.</p>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>

      <!-- Right Column -->
      <div class="space-y-8">
        <section class="rounded-3xl border border-indigo-950/20 bg-slate-900/60 p-6 space-y-4 shadow-xl">
          <h3 class="font-display text-lg font-black text-slate-900 dark:text-white flex items-center space-x-2">
            <span class="text-purple-500">📜</span>
            <span>HISTORY</span>
          </h3>
          <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm text-slate-650 dark:text-slate-355 leading-relaxed font-semibold">
            First described by Goethe (Theory of Colours). It remains a fundamental demonstration of perceptual processing and cognitive framing.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
